Instructions

1. Set relevant file path in the pf3k_antigen.Rmd including functionally annotated with SNPeff (http://snpeff.sourceforge.net/) and hard filtering as shown in manuscripts (figure S1). 

2. Obtain CDS Reference sequence in FastA format.

3. Input relevant information to antigen_targets.txt according to described format. 

4. Run analysis using run_analysis.sh script.

The contents of these repo are custom-tailored to our setup in R 3.5.2 environment and workflow 
(i.e. I make no promises that they may work for you), but I made them publicly available.
